    Number: 53
Title: Remorse
---
When I had you, I wasn’t devoted.
My piety greater than my love,
my caution outran my joy.
Moreover, being cold in nature and hounded by poverty,
I didn’t ease you in illness.
Now that you’re gone,
tears of regret are greater than the distress of separation.
